<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-16T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-16T08:00:00-05:00" n="126" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862.857/42: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Antofagasta</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Adams</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Antofagasta</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-16T09:00:00-04:00">December
                                    16, 1939—9 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 10:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Merchant vessel said to be German <hi rend="italic">Dusseldorf</hi> lying
                            at anchor 5 miles off shore at Antofagasta brought here this morning
                            under custody of British warship believed to be H.M.S. <hi rend="italic">Despatch</hi> lying in the harbor.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Adams</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>